{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year= 2008 |Team= North Texas Mean Green |Image= UNT Lettermark.png |ImageSize= 200 |Conference=Sun Belt Conference |Division= |ShortConference=Sun Belt |CoachRank= |APRank= |Record= 1â11 |ConfRecord= 0â7 |HeadCoach=[[Todd Dodge]] |OffCoach= Todd Ford |DefCoach= [[Gary DeLoach]] |OScheme= [[Offensive philosophy (American football)#The Spread|Spread Option]] |DScheme= [[4-3]] |StadiumArena=[[Fouts Field]] |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{2008 Sun Belt football standings}} The '''2008 North Texas Mean Green football team''' will represent the [[University of North Texas]] in the [[2008 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2008]] [[college football]] season. The 2008 season will be the team's second under Head Coach [[Todd Dodge]] with [[Gary DeLoach]] hired in the off-season as the new defensive coordinator replacing Ron Mendoza.<ref>[http://www.meangreensports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?SPSID=9058&SPID=562&DB_OEM_ID=1800&ATCLID=1375236 Dodge Names Gary DeLoach Defensive Coordinator - North Texas Mean Green Athletics<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The Mean Green play their home games on campus at [[Fouts Field]] in [[Denton, Texas]].
